{
  "_meta": {
    "description": "Heuristic financial-distress scoring on currently-active Chinese A-share IT companies (2022-2024). Higher score = more severe distress signals. Companies with score >= 8 are practical default candidates that may warrant target=1 relabelling after manual verification.",
    "window_years": "2022-2024",
    "units": "all financial metrics in millions CNY",
    "scoring_rules": {
      "neg_equity_any_year": 5,
      "neg_ni_>= 2_of_3yrs": 3,
      "neg_cfo_>= 2_of_3yrs": 2,
      "cash_<5pct_cl_>= 2_of_3yrs": 2,
      "total_debt_>70pct_assets_>= 2_of_3yrs": 1,
      "rev_decline_>30pct_>= 2_of_3yrs": 1
    },
    "verification_steps": [
      "Cross-check ticker via akshare stock_zh_a_st_em (current ST/*ST flag — financial-distress warning)",
      "Cross-check stock_info_sz_delist / stock_info_sh_delist (recent forced-delisting events)",
      "Verify exit reason was financial distress, NOT M&A or voluntary delisting (see project_passport.txt 1.3)",
      "If verified default, relabel source_class -> default_delisted, target -> 1 in cn_panel_enriched.csv"
    ],
    "caveats": [
      "Wind data may classify these as active because the panel was snapshotted at a point in time.",
      "Heuristic flags are descriptive of distress, not causal proof of default.",
      "A-share defaults are rare due to PRC state support; many distressed firms get bailed out / restructured rather than delisted (see project_passport.txt section 2 — China differs from Russia in this regard)."
    ]
  },
